# Slack feedback (local dev only)
# -------------------------------
# 1. In Slack: Apps → Incoming Webhooks → Add to workspace → copy Webhook URL.
# 2. In salt_app/, create a file named `.env.local` (gitignored via `*.local`) with exactly:
#
#    SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/TEAM/BOT/TOKEN
#
# 3. Stop and restart `npm run dev` so Vite reloads env and the dev proxy can forward
#    POST /api/slack-feedback → that URL (see vite-plugins/slack-webhook-proxy-plugin.js).
#
# Never commit `.env.local` or paste a real webhook into tracked files.

# Netlify production
# ------------------
# A static deploy cannot handle POST /api/slack-feedback. This repo includes
# `netlify.toml` + `netlify/functions/slack-feedback.mjs` so `/api/slack-feedback`
# is rewritten to a serverless function (same path the app already uses).
#
# In Netlify: set **Base directory** to `salt_app` (if the repo root is bi-react),
# then add the same env vars as above under Site settings → Environment variables:
# SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL, GOOGLE_SHEETS_WEBAPP_URL, SLACK_BOT_TOKEN, SLACK_FEEDBACK_CHANNEL_ID.
# Redeploy after changing secrets.

# Screenshot → Slack (optional; dev proxy + Netlify function)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Incoming webhooks cannot attach binary files. To post the feedback screenshot
# after the text message, create a Slack app with Bot token scope files:write
# (invite the bot to the channel). Then add to `.env.local` **or** Netlify env:
#
#    SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
#    SLACK_FEEDBACK_CHANNEL_ID=C0123456789
#
# Restart `npm run dev`. The client sends `screenshot: { filename, dataUrl }` in
# the same JSON POST; the proxy uploads via files.getUploadURLExternal /
# files.completeUploadExternal. Use the same pattern in production behind your API.

# Google Sheet — Feature requests only (via Apps Script web app)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Every submission still goes to Slack. When the user picks “Feature request”, the proxy
# also POSTs JSON { featureRequestSheet: { ... } } to append a row on the “Feedback” tab.
#
# 1. Open reference_google_apps_script/feedback-feature-append.gs — copy into Apps Script,
#    bound to the workbook (or standalone with the same spreadsheet ID).
# 2. Deploy → Web app → Execute as: Me → Who has access: Anyone (or your org policy).
# 3. Add to `.env.local`:
#
#    GOOGLE_SHEETS_WEBAPP_URL=https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfyc.../exec
#
# 4. Restart `npm run dev`.
#
# If this URL is unset, feature requests still post to Slack only; the API returns
# { ok: true, sheetsWarning: "..." }. If append fails, Slack still succeeds.
